---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/page/PageHero.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Cookies | Virtual Ventures"
  description="Cookie and local storage notes for Virtual Ventures, including gallery likes, Google Fonts, Cloudflare and future tools."
  showFooterBreadcrumbs={false}
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Data Notes"
    title="Cookies"
    description="A clear note about cookies, local storage, outside services and future tools on Virtual Ventures."
  />

  <main class="page-shell">
    <section class="page-intro">
      <p class="eyebrow">Cookies and storage</p>
      <h1>Tiny browser crumbs</h1>
      <p>
        This page explains the small technical bits that may be stored or loaded
        when you visit Virtual Ventures.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Current cookie position</h2>
        <p>
          In the code checked for this draft, Virtual Ventures does not appear to
          set marketing cookies, advertising cookies or customer account cookies.
        </p>
        <p>
          Cloudflare settings may still add security or performance behaviour
          outside the GitHub codebase, so the Cloudflare dashboard should be
          checked before this page is published.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-right">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Local gallery likes</h2>
        <p>
          The gallery uses browser local storage to remember whether you liked a
          gallery item. The key begins with "vv-gallery-liked:" and is stored on
          your own device.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is not a public like system, not a customer account, and not a
          mailing list. You can clear it by clearing site data in your browser.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Google Fonts</h2>
        <p>
          The site currently loads fonts from Google Fonts. This means your
          browser may request font files from Google when pages load.
        </p>
        <p>
          A more privacy-conscious future option would be to self-host the font
          files instead, as long as the font licences allow it.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-right">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Videos and embeds</h2>
        <p>
          No YouTube embeds were found in the current code checked for this
          draft. If videos are added later, Virtual Ventures should prefer
          privacy-conscious embeds, lazy loading, or click-to-load video blocks
          where possible.
        </p>
        <p>
          If a video is only linked, clicking it takes you to YouTube or another
          platform with its own privacy and cookie rules.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Future tools</h2>
        <p>
          If analytics, Turnstile, a working contact form, email subscription,
          comments, checkout, video embeds or other third-party tools are added,
          this page should be updated before those tools go live.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-closing-card">
      <p>
        Cookie pages are not one-and-done parchment. They need checking whenever
        the site gains a new tool.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
